      "author": "github-actions[bot]",
      "description": "## What's new\n\nThis release adds the Connection Intelligence workbench: a single Obsidian side panel for exploring semantic similarity, missing links, bridges, local links, and note diagnostics from the active note.\n\n### Connection workbench\n\n- Added a graph-backed side panel with tabs for Best, Missing Links, Bridges, Similar, Links, and Diagnostics.\n- Added intent-specific ranking so each tab answers a different question instead of reusing one generic score.\n- Added synchronized graph/list highlighting, collapsed result rows, expandable evidence snippets, and drag-ready Obsidian wiki links.\n\n### Better recommendation signals\n\n- Added graph analysis metrics for common neighbours, Jaccard, Adamic-Adar, resource allocation, preferential attachment, cosine similarity, and co-citation support.\n- Improved Missing Links scoring with semantic, title/full-text, graph, and co-citation signals.\n- Improved Bridges scoring so the list can show broader candidates while the graph stays focused on the top bridge paths.\n- Kept Similar aligned with canonical semantic similarity order.\n\n### Obsidian integration\n\n- Added local expandable link graphs with backlink/outgoing expansion controls.\n- Improved Obsidian-native link handling, hover previews, source path resolution, Supercharged Links rendering, and snippet opening.\n- Added note diagnostics for link structure, discovery inputs, text shape, metadata, quote blocks, callouts, reading time, and page estimates.\n\n### Quality\n\n- Added focused tests for graph analysis, workbench tab behavior, link handling, diagnostics, and text statistics.\n\n**Full Changelog**: https://github.com/flowing-abyss/obsidian-hybrid-search-plugin/compare/v0.4.1...v0.5.0",
